Question 1 – Simple Decision (Basic if)
Scenario:
A program asks the user to enter their age.
If the age entered is 18 or above, display:
"You are eligible to vote."

Question 2 – Condition Checking (Basic if)
Scenario:
A shop offers a discount for customers who spend more than RM100.
If total purchase is greater than 100, display:
"You get a discount!"

Question 3 – Pass or Fail (if-else)
Scenario:
If score is 50 or above, display "Pass", otherwise display "Fail".

Question 4 – Grade Classification (Nested if-else)
Scenario:
80 and above : Grade A
60–79       : Grade B
50–59       : Grade C
Below 50    : Fail

Question 5 – Access Control System (Nested if-else)
Scenario:
If user is staff:
    If access level >= 5 → Access granted
    Else → Access denied: insufficient level
If not staff → Access denied: staff only


